    "(2019) Planktonic foraminiferal species recognition 32,626 images of modern planktonic Foraminifera Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs) Accuracy 87.4% VGG16 cannot fully leverage the complex spatial relationships and subtle morphological features unique to microfossils, and the absence of data augmentation skews the model's performance toward more frequently represented classes de Lima et al. (2019) Fusulinids classification 3119 RGB images MobileNet V2 Inception V3 Accuracy 91.2% The model is trained on a curated dataset and controlled input images, achieving high accuracy in CNN-assisted geological analysis, which may not reflect the model's performance in more complex, real-world scenarios Pires de Lima et al.",
